<H3> <TI>   Urges Participation in UN Missions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Urges Participation in UN Missions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706152594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1339 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DDP/ADN) -- Defense Minister Volker Ruehe 
(Christian Democratic Union) is pressing for Bundeswehr 
participation in international UN missions. In a speech marking 
the renaming of the General Schwartzkopf barracks as the 
Lieutenant General Count von Baudissin barracks, Ruehe called 
for German "sharing of responsibility for the protection of 
freedom, against genocide and against disregard for human 
rights." 
  If Germany does not take on this responsibility, then it is 
isolating itself in the community of nations. International 
Bundeswehr missions are therefore not a secondary military 
issue. They take account of increased international 
responsibility and are decisive for determining Germany's 
abilities as a member of Europe and its credibility as an 
alliance partner. 
  Ruehe added that during their UN missions in Iraq, Bosnia, 
Cambodia, and Somalia the Bundeswehr soldiers had "proven their 
military capability and their great ability to empathize." In 
this way they visibly showed their support for the values of the 
constitution and solidarity in the community of nations. 

</TEXT>

