<H3> <TI>   Russia's Rybkin Praises Relations With Germans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Rybkin Praises Relations With Germans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806094094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0833 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Moscow (DDP/ADN) -- Ivan Rybkin, chairman of the 
Russian parliament [State Duma], described relations 
between Germany and Russia as exemplary. "There are good 
opportunities to further develop the constructive and 
businesslike relationship which also exists between the two 
countries' parliaments," Rybkin said today in an interview with 
the DDP/ADN news agency in Moscow. This aim will also be served 
by his first visit to Germany as chairman of the State Duma. 
Rybkin will come to Germany next week on Wednesday [11 June] as 
the head of a Duma delegation. 
  Germany's experiences in the development of a democratic and 
economically strong social state could be very useful for 
Russia. "In this connection, we want to acquaint ourselves with 
the move of the economy in the former East Germany from central 
planning to market economy principles," said Rybkin, who was 
elected chairman of the Duma on 14 January. The solution of 
this problem is a priority for Russia, too, to further advance 
reforms. 
  Rybkin, who described his relationship with President Boris 
Yeltsin as "very good and constructive," came out in favor of 
continuing the democratic and economic reforms in his country. 
However, the changes must be well considered and implemented 
with the required social provision. "The time of quick 
decisions is past," the Duma chairman stressed. Russians have 
the capabilities and the will decisively to improve their lives. 
"But this requires effort from everyone every day -- from the 
president down to the ordinary citizen." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

