<H3> <TI>   Export List Increases Control in Sensitive Areas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Export List Increases Control in Sensitive Areas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806094694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0836 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Export controls in sensitive areas 
are to be intensified. This, according to the Federal Economics 
Ministry, is the aim of the revised version of the export list, 
which the federal cabinet approved today. The revised version 
also brought with it both an easing of export regulations and a 
simplification of procedures. The raising of the limits in the 
computer and electronics sectors is worth particular emphasis. 
  This will noticeably reduce the number of export permits 
required from the Federal Export Office. This will, in its 
turn, take a considerable burden off the export sector. The 
situation following the abolition of the common export controls 
by the Western world for goods suitable for military purposes 
(COCOM) was given consideration when the new version of the 
export list was drawn up. 

</TEXT>

