<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Reaches Agreement With Pannella </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Reaches Agreement With Pannella </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706163794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1554 GMT 
7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An agreement has been reached between the government 
and Marco Pannella. The latter and his supporters will now form 
part of the ruling government coalition. The news was released 
during a joint news conference given by Silvio Berlusconi and 
Pannella. Berlusconi said that the agreement "is a visible 
signal that the government is of the center." Pannella stressed 
that some points of the agreement "could bind us for the entire 
legislative term." 
  The agreement, Berlusconi stressed, is a reply to the demand 
for change expressed by the country. The agreement envisions, 
among other things, a single round for elections and 
establishing a UN tribunal in order to try those responsible for 
crimes against humanity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

