<F P=102>   TA0706182794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1600 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0706182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ankara, June 7 (A.A.) -- Foreign Ministry Deputy 
Undersecretary Tugay Ulucevik said on Tuesday [7 June] that 
Turkey called the United Nations Security Council members to 
have a positive approach toward an agreement on Cyprus that will 
not pave the way to destroy a possible agreement. 
  A Foreign Ministry statement said Ulucevik met Pakistani, 
British, Chinese, Russian, U.S., Oman, New Zealand, Spanish, 
Argentinian, and Brazilian ambassadors on June 6 and 7 
separately and conveyed to them that Turkey supported Turkish 
Republic of Northern Cyprus' constructive attitude toward 
confidence-building measures during a negotiation process. 
  The statement said the UN secretary general's report failed 
to help find a lasting solution to the Cyprus problem. 
  The statement said Ulucevik wanted the ambassadors to take 
the May 30 improvements into consideration adding that Turkey 
expected to find a realistic and balanced solution that is based 
on equality in Cyprus problem. [passage omitted] 

