Network in Greek GMT 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0706121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cyprus and Egypt signed a security agreement this 
morning aimed at combating organized crime, drug trafficking, 
and international terrorism. The agreement was signed by 
Justice and Public Order Minister Alekos Egangelou and by Nassar 
Zahir, Egypt's assistant interior minister, who began a five-day 
visit to Cyprus yesterday. 
  In a statement after the signing of the agreement, Mr. 
Evangelou praised the importance of the agreement and also 
referred to the close relations between the two countries. 

