<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Council Resumes Debate on UN Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Council Resumes Debate on UN Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0806084194 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0700 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0806084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Council convened a meeting 
approximately one-half hour ago to continue discussion on the 
situation after the deadlock in the confidence-building measures 
[CBM's] and the UN report which established the lack of 
political will by the Turkish side. 
  The debate opened last Friday [3 June] and President Glavkos 
Kliridhis verbally submitted suggestions. There was an initial 
exchange of views on the UN report and the future of the Cyprus 
issue. 
  Attendees at today's meeting include Ioannis Matsis and 
Alekos Markidhis on behalf of the Democratic Rally [DISI]; 
Dhimitrios Khristofias and Andreas Khristou representing AKEL 
[Restorative Party of the Working People]; Spiros Kiprianou and 
Tasos Papadhopoulos representing DIKO [Democratic Party]; and 
Vasos Lissaridhis and Takis Khatzidhimitriou on behalf of EDEK 
[United Democratic Union of Cyprus]. Also present at the 
meeting are House of Representatives President Alexis Galanos, 
Government Spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis, Attorney General 
Mikhail Triandafillidhis, and Deputy Minister to President 
Pandelis Kouros. 

</TEXT>

