<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkey's Ciller Criticizes UN Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkey's Ciller Criticizes UN Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706163294 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1030 GMT 7 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkish Prime Minister Tansu Ciller has stated that 
the report UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali submitted to the 
Security Council will act as a deterrent in achieving a just 
solution to the Cyprus issue and even cause a deadlock. 
Recalling that President Rauf Denktas had accepted those 
agreements reached at the meetings held with UN representatives 
in Vienna which were within the framework of the 
confidence-building measures, Ciller continued: The Turkish 
side agrees to the package but the report creates an obstacle in 
the way to a just solution to the Cyprus issue. 
  Addressing the True Path Party National Assembly caucus in 
Ankara, Ciller discussed the Cyprus issue and criticized the UN 
secretary general's report. Ciller indicated that previous 
experiences have proved that it is impossible to achieve a 
solution to the Cyprus issue by coercion and threats. 
  Stating that Turkey supports a just, realistic, and viable 
Cyprus solution based on the equality of both communities, 
Ciller stressed that Turkey will continue to support the Turkish 
Cypriots to the best of its ability. 

</TEXT>

