<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Claims Called `Ridiculous, Unfounded' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Claims Called `Ridiculous, Unfounded' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0706183894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1700 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0706183894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today said 
that Greece condemns every act of violence and terrorism but it 
does not accept becoming the victim of an orchestrated effort to 
export Turkey's domestic problems to Greece. 
  Venizelos repeated that no office of the PKK [Workers Party 
of Kurdistan] operates in Athens, and once again described the 
Turkish claims as ridiculous, unfounded, and slanderous. 
Venizelos said that President Konstandinos Karamanlis will soon 
give his answer to Turkish President Suleyman Demirel's letter 
and the Turkish claims regarding the PKK action. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

