<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Antiauthority Struggle' Responsibile for Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Antiauthority Struggle' Responsibile for Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606100994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0900 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0606100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shortly after midnight two cars from the Forest 
Department were the target of a bomb attack outside the Ministry 
of Agriculture on Akharnon Street. An unidentified caller to a 
private radio station said the terrorist group Antiauthority 
Struggle was claiming responsibility for the attack. 

</TEXT>

