<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Balladur Meets Clinton, Praises Policies, Actions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Balladur Meets Clinton, Praises Policies, Actions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706143494 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1400 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706143494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bill Clinton spent an extra hour at the prime 
minister's office with Edouard Balladur. The U.S. President 
talked about the major current issues, such as GATT, the G-7, 
Bosnia, and Europe. 
  Clinton and Balladur also talked with journalists for a 
while. The French prime minister seized this opportunity to say 
how much he appreciated U.S. security policy in Europe: 
  [Begin Balladur recording] I still have confidence in the 
U.S. Administration and in the actions of President Clinton. We 
may not hold the same views on some issues -- the opposite would 
be surprising -- but what is of the utmost importance is our 
common desire to maintain peace and security in Europe. 
  I must say that I found President Clinton to be very 
open-minded with regard to European issues and the need for 
Europe to be better organized. This is what he repeated earlier 
as we were finishing our lunch. 
  I think that most of the reasons why we may have 
misunderstood each other have now disappeared. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

