<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Calls For Rwanda Task Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Calls For Rwanda Task Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706193794 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1745 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, Silvio Berlusconi paid a visit to the 
Bambino Gesu hospital where 11 Rwandan children have been 
admitted. When asked about the possible solutions to the Rwandan 
tragedy, Berlusconi said: 
  [Begin Berlusconi recording] I believe that if we have a 
true 
conscience as world citizens, then I believe we must find a way 
to intervene. We must find a way to intervene adequately, 
quickly, in an effective way; I believe that the world, those 
countries that are democratic and civilized, must find a way of 
setting up an army, a permanent task force for exactly this type 
of intervention. This task force could be made up perhaps of 
ordinary troops or volunteers. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

