<H3> <TI>   Egyptian Assistant Interior Minister Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egyptian Assistant Interior Minister Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606175694 Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY in English 0839 GMT 
6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0606175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Larnaca, June 6 (CNA)--General Nassar Zahir, 
Egyptian Assistant Minister of Interior, arrived here Monday [6 
June] morning for a five-day visit. 
  Zahir, who is accompanied by Brigadier Majdi Sharif, will 
sign tomorrow an agreement on security matters with Cypriot 
Minister of Justice and Public Order Alekos Evangelou. 
  The agreement will focus in particular on cooperation in 
combating organised crime, drug trafficking and international 
terrorism. 
  It also provides for the exchange of information on security 
matters, on scientific issues, on aliens and forged documents. 
The agreement allows for exchange training programmes between 
the two countries. 
  The Egyptian official will have a meeting with Dinos 
Mikhalidhis, minister of interior and police chief, Andreas 
Potamaris, and other senior members of the Cyprus police force 
to discuss the implementation of the agreement. 
  Zahir leaves on Friday. 

</TEXT>

