<H3> <TI>   NATO Session Opens in Istanbul; Balanzino Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO Session Opens in Istanbul; Balanzino Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0706183294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0706183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Meetings to be attended by the foreign ministers of 
NATO as well as the North Atlantic Cooperation Council -- 
members of the former East Bloc -- will begin in Istanbul on 9 
June. NATO Deputy Secretary General Sergio Balanzino, who will 
attend the meeting, arrived in Istanbul today. 
  Balanzino will chair the meetings on behalf of NATO 
Secretary 
General Manfred Woerner, who is unable to arrive in Turkey 
because of illness. The alliance's relations with the former 
East Bloc countries, especially with Russia, constitutes the 
main item on the agenda of the NATO foreign ministers meeting to 
be held on 9 June. The meeting will also focus on the war in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and other regional and international issues. 
  The foreign ministers of NATO and former East Bloc countries 
will meet on 10 June. The foreign ministers of some 40 
countries are expected to attend this meeting. 

</TEXT>

