<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Calls For Disarmament Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas Calls For Disarmament Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0306164494 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1530 GMT 3 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0306164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Rauf Denktas has called on the Greek 
Cypriot side for mutual disarmament, stressing that this is the 
wish and will of the Turkish side. Denktas inaugurated the 
central siren system established by the Civil Defense 
Organization. 
  In a speech which was broadcast through the siren system he 
inaugurated today, Denktas called for mutual disarmament. 
Denktas said: Come let us sign a disarmament agreement and let 
our people be comfortable. Let us be good neighbors and let 
these good neighborly relations lead to peace. This is our wish 
and will. Armament is of no help to anybody and only instigates 
enmity. Within this awareness, I repeat my call for peace on 
this historical day, for signing an agreement on condition that 
the flag of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus is not 
lowered from its flag-post. Indicating that the whole world 
knows the Turkish side's feelings concerning this issue, Denktas 
added that he wanted the Greek Cypriots to be aware of the 
Turkish side's sentiments as well. 

</TEXT>

