<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Column Criticizes UK-U.S. `Support' for Turkish Side </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Column Criticizes UK-U.S. `Support' for Turkish Side </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0906090794 Nicosia ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 9 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> NC0906090794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Views" column: "There Is No More Margin..."] </F>
  [Text] It is not difficult for one to realize that the 
United States and Britain encourage the new Turkish maneuver to 
block the promotion of new, more effective, processes on the 
Cyprus issue. A plan to amend Butrus-Ghali's report to the UN 
Security Council supposedly to include Denktas' intentions is 
already under way in New York. It is obvious that this attempt 
aims at changing the climate that has been created following the 
points made in the Butrus-Ghali report regarding Turkish 
intransigence. 
  Once again, the United States and Britain rush to support 
the 
Turkish side. Once again, the United States and Britain attempt 
to prevent developments which are not satisfactory to Ankara and 
Denktas. Again and again, the United States and Britain render 
useless, or at least attempt to render useless, every 
possibility to steer the Cyprus issue onto the right course. It 
is natural that these attempts concern us and we should deal 
with them in a decisive and vigorous manner, because we do not 
have the margin to be dragged into a process which derails the 
Cyprus issue even further from its correct direction and 
framework. 

</TEXT>

