GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0806184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Prosperity Party [PP] leader Necmettin Erbakan has 
said that the real aim of Poised Hammer is to divide Turkey. 
Its mandate should not be extended again, he said. 
  Addressing a PP assembly group meeting, Erbakan alleged that 
it has been documented that Poised Hammer extends food and 
medical aid to the separatist terrorist organization PKK 
[Workers Party of Kurdistan]. 
  Erbakan also said that it is wrong to extend the state of 
emergency, which has been in effect for so long, by another four 
months. 
  [Begin Erbakan recording] We want every kind of freedom to 
reign in every part of our country. We hold our country's unity 
and integrity above all else. While upholding our country's 
unity and integrity, however, we want the rules to be the same 
throughout the country. [end recording] 
  Erbakan charged that constitutional amendments are the 
business of the parliament not of the government. He welcomed 
the decision to set up an interparty committee to prepare the 
constitutional amendments. 

