<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Erzincan Governor: 54 `Terrorists' Die in 5 Months </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0806165794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1525 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0806165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Erzincan, June 8 (A.A.) -- Fifty-four terrorists 
have been killed during operations carried out by security 
forces in the last five months in eastern Erzincan Province, it 
was reported on Monday [6 June]. 
  Erzincan Governor Recep Yazicioglu told the ANATOLIAN AGENCY 
that the operations were carried out in the rural areas and in 
the town center, without interruption and that the organization 
was crippled in the region. 
  `Twenty-five people who provided logistic and material 
support to a terrorist organization were also captured and 
arrested,' he added. 
  He also said that handguns, machine guns, ammunition and 
prohibited publications were also seized, adding four security 
force members were also killed. 
  Yazicioglu also stressed that the arrested terrorists' 
average age was 16 and this shows the organization is having 
problems recruiting new members. 

</TEXT>

