Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkey: NATO `Expansion With Time' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkey: NATO `Expansion With Time' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0806163894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1555 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0806163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Istanbul, June 8 (A.A.) -- Foreign Minister 
Hikmet Cetin on Wednesday [8 June] said that Turkey supports the 
expansion with time, of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization 
adding however that NATO-Russia relations should not overshadow 
its ties with other members. 
  He was speaking to reporters prior to a NATO ministers 
council meeting and the North Atlantic Cooperation Council 
meetings which will start in Istanbul and will end on Friday. 
  Reminding that Russia accepted the Partnership for Peace 
plan 
during the meeting last January, he added that the most 
important factor there is that former Warsaw Pact members and 
Russia will sign a single agreement. 
  A joint document is expected to be signed at the end of the 
NATO meetings and paragraphs directly concerning Russia are 
expected to take place in the meeting. [sentence as received] 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

