<H3> <TI>   Mongolian Minister Signs Commercial Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mongolian Minister Signs Commercial Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1006032394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1223 GMT 9 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1006032394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 9 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Staying in 
Canada on an official visit at the invitation of his Canadian 
counterpart the Minister of External Relations of Mongolia T. 
Gombosuren has signed on 8 June in Ottawa the Mongolian-Canadian 
intergovernmental agreement on trade bargains. At the same day 
he met with the president of the parliamentary Senate of Canada 
R. Leblanc and handed in to him a message by the chairman of the 
Mongolian parliament was holding an exchange of opinions on 
issues of the development of bilateral relations with secretary 
of state of the Canadian minister of foreign relations and 
international trade, Legislator R. Chan and delivered him a 
message by the Mongolian prime minister. [sentence as received] 
  T. Gombosuren is staying in Canada since June 5. 

</TEXT>

