<H3> <TI>   RAI Chairman: Controversy Over </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RAI Chairman: Controversy Over </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906210294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1736 GMT 
9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The matter is closed", said Claudio Dematte, the 
chairman of the RAI [Italian Broadcasting Corporation], who was 
referring to the storm surrounding the recent remarks of Silvio 
Berlusconi. 
  The prime minister "told me that his plan is very clear: The 
RAI cannot be progovernment or antigovernment," said Dematte, 
who along with RAI Managing Director Gianni Locatelli, met 
Berlusconi at the Saxa Rubra television center. "We agreed to 
see each other in order to begin work immediately on the 
regulations governing the RAI and its reorganization plan. 
That's all." 

