<H3> <TI>   Spokesman on Papoulias-Cetin Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman on Papoulias-Cetin Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0906124494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0906124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said a 
short while ago that yesterday's remarks by Turkish Foreign 
Minister Hikmet Cetin were carefully expressed and more 
moderate. The Greek Government, Venizelos stressed, considers 
the Turkish foreign minister's remarks as an attitude of 
decreased tension, within the more general climate of 
cultivating artificial tension with the neighboring country. 
  The government spokesman also referred to the meeting 
between 
Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias and Cetin later today in 
Istanbul, and said that the issues that will be raised by the 
Greek side include provocations against the Ecumenical 
Patriarchate and also the ridiculous and unfounded claims by 
Turkey regarding a relationship between Greece and the illegal 
Workers Party of Kurdistan [PKK]. 

</TEXT>

