<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Briefs Press on Papoulias-Velayati Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Briefs Press on Papoulias-Velayati Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906124894 Tehran IRNA in English 1228 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Athens, June 9, IRNA -- Public order and security 
were among the issues which Greek Foreign Minister Karolos 
Papoulias discussed with his Iranian counterpart 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati in Tehran, Greek Government spokesman Evangelos 
Venizelos told a regular press briefing Thursday [9 June]. 
  In reply to a Greek journalist's question if Papoulias 
raised 
the issue of "terrorism" during his talks, Venizelos replied 
that he discussed a number of topics with Velayati and other 
Iranian officials including the issues of public order and 
security. 
  Papoulias Wednesday flew to Istanbul after a two-day visit 
to 
the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Last month the british newspaper INDEPENDENT alleged that 
members of the greek guerrilla organisation `17 November' had 
met Iranian officials. 
  The news was also reported in the Greek press. Tehran 
rejected the report as "baseless and false." 

</TEXT>

