<H3> <TI>   Cetin Says Cyprus CBM Package `Not Dead Yet' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Says Cyprus CBM Package `Not Dead Yet' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1006081894 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0430 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1006081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has declared that as 
far as Turkey is concerned, the confidence-building measures 
[CBM] package in Cyprus is not dead yet. During a chat with 
reporters in Istanbul last night, Cetin responded to Greek 
Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias' statement that the CBM's are 
dead. 
  Commenting on the negotiating process concerning the CBM's, 
Cetin declared: The package is not fully alive, but it has not 
died yet. As far as we are concerned, the process is continuing. 
  In his news conference in Istanbul yesterday, Papoulias 
blamed the Turkish side for the failure to implement the CBM 
package and claimed that the package is dead. 

</TEXT>

