<H3> <TI>   Cetin Discusses Straits Rules With Russia's Kozyrev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Discusses Straits Rules With Russia's Kozyrev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1006074194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2120 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1006074194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has declared that if 
the new statute concerning passage from the Istanbul Strait is 
not enforced, a city of 10 million will be in jeopardy, and 
Turkey will in no way allow this. 
  Cetin met with Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, who 
is currently in Turkey for the North Atlantic Cooperation 
Council meeting. In a statement, Cetin reported that the 
straits statute was discussed during the meeting. Cetin said 
that he explained to the Russian foreign minister that the new 
statute regulating passage from the Bosporus does not violate 
the Montreux Convention. Cetin declared: 
  [Begin Cetin recording] If necessary, we can clarify some of 
the issues again and explain that they do not violate the 
Montreux Convention. It is possible that some technical issues 
are not entirely clear, but Turkey cannot allow a city of 10 
million people to be threatened. A new arrangement is 
absolutely necessary, and the Russians also concede this point. 
[end recording] 
  Cetin added that the Azerbaijani-Armenian conflict and the 
Karkuk-Yumurtalik oil pipeline issues were also discussed with 
Kozyrev. 

</TEXT>

