<H3> <TI>   Central Bank on Foreign Trade Deficit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank on Foreign Trade Deficit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0906174194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1555 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0906174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 9 (A.A.) -- Turkey's current 
transactions deficit for the first quarter of this year 
increased by 22.7 percent compared to the same period last year, 
it was reported on Thursday [9 June]. 
  According to a statment by the Central Bank, this amounted 
to 
1.14 billion U.S. dollars, compared to last year's 925 million 
dollars. 
  In the balance of payments sheet, foreign trade deficit 
decreased by 17.8 percent when compared to the same period last 
year. 
  The foreign trade deficit last year for the same period was 
2.2 billion dollars compared to this year's 1.8 billion dollars. 
  In this decrease while imports stayed at the same level, the 
export increased by 4 percent. 

</TEXT>

