Cyprus, in the occupied areas. 
  In a statement at the Ledra Palace Hotel roadblock, Feissel 
said the clarifications basically concerned the issue of access 
to Famagusta. He said there are some positive developments in 
comparison to the positions expressed by Denktas on 6 May, but 
added that it is uncertain if these developments will lead to 
the desired outcome. The UN envoy said he will brief the UN 
secretary general by tomorrow, who will then inform the Security 
Council. 

