  [Text] Mulhouse (DPA) -- Germany and France will take over 
the presidency in the European Union (EU), which both countries 
will hold one after the other for almost a year as of 1 July, 
with a well coordinated work program. This was stressed by 
Chancellor Helmut Kohl and French President Francois Mitterrand 
at the conclusion of their 63d summit in Mulhouse, Alsace, on 
