<F P=106> [Report signed MTH: "Delors' Succession: Tindemans Comes </F>
Out in Favor of Dehaene"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 2 Jun (ANP) -- On Wednesday [1 June], Leo 
Tindemans of the CVP [Flemish Christian People's Party], who is 
chairman of the Christian Democrats in the European Parliament 
(EP), announced on a Netherlands commercial television station 
that he was in favor of Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene 
succeeding Jacques Delors as president of the European 
Commission (EC). 
  The statements by Tindemans were greeted with astonishment 
by 
both his entourage and by Dutch members of his political group. 
The former Belgian prime minister will announce his choice to 
the new group that is elected as soon as it takes up its duties 
after the European elections next 9 and 12 June. The EPP 
[Group of the European People's Party] chairman Wilfried Martens 
said he was "embarrassed" by the statement made by Tindemans, 
for there had been no consultation with him, nor any decision 
within the party on a potential candidate to succeed Delors. 
  Up to now, the only candidate declared by the PPE group is 
former Netherlands Prime Minister Ruud Lubbers, who has 
officially submitted his candidacy to succeed Delors, something 
which the Belgian prime minister has not done. 
  "I would not attach too much importance to these 
statements," 
Martens affirmed. 
  According to him, if the PPE decides to present a single 
candidate for the post of EC president, it will make its 
decision at the summit meeting of the heads of government and 
chairmen of Christian Democratic parties to be held in Brussels 
on 22 June. 

</TEXT>

