<F P=106> [Press release issued by the UK Ministry of Defence: </F>
"Nuclear Detargeting"] 
  [Text] In accordance with the agreement signed by the Prime 
Minister and President Yeltsin in Moscow on 15 February, all of 
the United Kingdom's strategic missiles were detargeted by 30 
May, the guidance computers on UK strategic missiles no longer 
routinely hold targeting information, and the primary target 
assignments held in readiness for insertion into the missiles 
will be points in the open ocean. 
  This step is a positive demonstration of the developing 
cooperative relationship between the United Kingdom and the 
Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

