<H3> <TI>   Bonn `Concerned' About Nuclear Proliferation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn `Concerned' About Nuclear Proliferation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806150294 Hamburg DPA in German 1400 GMT 8 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0806150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Federal Government is concerned 
about the proliferation of carrier missiles and mass destruction 
weapons. An increasing number of Third World countries are 
trying to acquire such weapons, a report of the Federal 
Intelligence Office says, which was presented by State Minister 
in the Chancellor's Office Bernd Schmidbauer to the Cabinet on 
Wednesday [8 June]. 
  According to Government Spokesman Dieter Vogel, it is 
pointed 
out that North Korea is willing to sell its carrier systems to 
anyone who pays the necessary sum of money. It is to be assumed 
that more and more "threshold countries" are offering such 
systems and that missiles with a range of 1,000 km will already 
be available by the beginning of the next decade. The report 
comes to the conclusion that only a strict export regime and 
close international cooperation can prevent further 
proliferation. 

</TEXT>

